    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-31T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-31T07:00:00-05:00" n="568"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d568">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/586: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-31T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 31, 1935—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 31—1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>273. Have seen Kung this afternoon at the Minister’s instruction. Kung informed
                    me that he desired to accept American Government’s proposal regarding payment
                    silver, writing to that effect tomorrow morning.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Legation at Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
